# CareMind AI — Golden Rules

## File Size
- No file may exceed **350 lines**. If it grows beyond that, split it into sub-modules immediately (use `.part2.ts` suffix or extract a sub-service).

## Architecture
- Every external integration is behind an **interface (adapter pattern)**. Swapping vendors requires changing exactly one file and one env var.
- **No business logic in route handlers.** Routes call service functions; service functions call adapters/repositories.
- **Multi-tenancy is structural**: each org gets its own PostgreSQL database. Central DB holds only org registry, auth tokens, and billing.

## Security (non-negotiable)
- `patient_id`, `org_id`, `role` are **always resolved server-side from the JWT** — never trusted from client request body.
- All PHI-touching operations are **audit-logged** via `auditLog()` in `src/core/audit-logger.ts`.
- Passwords hashed with **bcrypt cost 12+**.
- Refresh tokens are **single-use and hashed** in DB — never stored in plain text.
- Vector search **always** includes `patient_id + org_id` filters. These are mandatory and cannot be bypassed.
- Recording only starts after **confirmed consent** in DB (`consentStatus = 'accepted'`).
- AI outputs **never** enter the knowledge base without `status = 'approved'`.

## TypeScript
- **Strict mode on.** No `any` without an explicit suppression comment explaining why.
- No implicit `any`. Prefer explicit types over inference for public function signatures.

## MVP Vendor Lock-In (do not deviate)
| Capability | MVP Provider |
|---|---|
| AI / LLM | OpenRouter only |
| Embeddings | Voyage AI only |
| Storage | MinIO only |
| Meetings | LiveKit only |
| STT | Deepgram only |
| OCR | Tesseract (+ poppler `pdftoppm` for PDF pages) only |
| Email | Resend only |
| PDF Export | Puppeteer only |
| Queue | BullMQ + Redis only |
| Database | PostgreSQL + pgvector only |

Do **not** create adapters, env vars, or Docker containers for alternative providers unless explicitly requested.

## Response Envelope
All API responses follow:
```json
// Success
{ "data": {...}, "meta": { "requestId": "...", "timestamp": "..." } }
// Error
{ "error": { "code": "...", "message": "...", "details": [...] } }
```
